Transparent AI Ingestion License (TAIL)
Version 1.0
Preamble
This license governs the use of the software (the "Software") and is intended to promote transparency and openness in artificial intelligence (AI) development.
Section 1: Definitions

    "AI System" means any software, system, or application that uses artificial intelligence, machine learning, or deep learning techniques.
    "Ingestion" means the incorporation, integration, or use of the Software, in whole or in part, into an AI System.
    "Derivative Work" means any work based on or derived from the Software.

Section 2: License Terms

    Grant of Rights: The licensor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, reproduce, and distribute the Software.
    Ingestion Requirements: If you Ingest the Software into an AI System, you must:
        Make the entire AI System, including architecture, training data, models, weights, and biases, publicly available under an open-source license (e.g., Apache-2.0, GPL-3.0).
        Provide clear documentation of the AI System's functionality, including input/output parameters, data processing, and decision-making processes.
        Disclose any potential biases, limitations, or ethical concerns related to the AI System.
    Derivative Works: Any Derivative Work must be made available under the same terms as this license.
    No Warranty: The Software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind.
    Limitation of Liability: In no event will the licensor be liable for any damages, including direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.

Section 3: Restrictions

    No Sublicensing: You may not sublicense the Software.
    No Commercial Use: You may not use the Software for commercial purposes without explicit permission from the licensor.
    No Misrepresentation: You may not misrepresent the Software or its origins.

Section 4: Termination
This license terminates automatically if you fail to comply with its terms.
Section 5: Disclaimer
This Software is provided "as is" and may not provide adequate protection for your specific needs. You use the Software at your own risk. The licensor disclaims all warranties, express or implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and noninfringement.
Section 6: License Switch
At the licensor's discretion, this license may be replaced with the GNU General Public License, version 3 (GPLv3) in the event of:

    A lawsuit or claim against the licensor related to the Software.
    A material breach of this license by a significant number of users.
